Paratypes : Female, 20.5 mm (
ZRC 50707
), same collection data as holotype
;
303 specimens : 14.0– 19.6 mm (
ZRC 50708
), same collection data as holotype
;
40 specimens : 14.1–19.3 mm ( CAS 224434 ), same collection data as holotype
;
40 specimens : 13.9–20.5 mm ( USNM 388753 ), same collection data as holotype
.

Head rounded, its length 3.9–4.1 times in standard length. Snout very short, its length only one-half of eye diameter. Eye large, in anterior half of head. Horizontal eye diameter 10 times in standard length. Barbels absent (as in most 
Danioinae
).

Mouth very small, jaws entirely in front of orbit (
Fig. 3
). When mouth is closed jaws are oriented at an angle of 45º upward. See discussion for remarks on “danioin notch.”
